President Obama announced his intent to nominate Michael E. Horowitz as Inspector General of the Department of Justice and Anneila I. Sargent as a member of the National Science Board of the National Science Foundation. He also announced his intent to appoint Betty Castor as a member of the J. William Fulbright Foreign Scholarship Board, Susan Ness as a member of the J. William Fulbright Foreign Scholarship Board, and Clement A. Price as Vice Chairman of the Advisory Council on Historic Preservation. These individuals bring diverse backgrounds and expertise to their respective roles and are dedicated to serving the American people.